PN,41701
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1776819790
OL,3,CFamily of UK's youngest blood
OL,4,Ctransfusion recipient express
OL,5,Cgratitude to donors
OL,7,FThe family of the UK's youngest ever
OL,8,Fblood transfusion recipient have said
OL,9,Fhow "lucky" they are as they expressed
OL,10,Ftheir "gratitude" to the donors whose
OL,11,Fspecialist blood is used the most for
OL,12,Fone of the rarest transfusions - given
OL,13,Fwhen a baby is still in the womb.
OL,15,FDoctors think Arthur Ransom from
OL,16,FCranleigh in Surrey is the youngest
OL,17,Fpatient in the UK to have had a blood
OL,18,Ftransfusion, delivered when his mother
OL,19,Fwas just 16 weeks pregnant.
OL,26,@qD@EOUqD@KO]rD@GOUrD@QO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1776819790
OL,3,CFamily of UK's youngest blood
OL,4,Ctransfusion recipient express
OL,5,Cgratitude to donors
OL,7,FWhen Arthur was around the size of an
OL,8,Favocado, doctors delivered the tiny
OL,9,Ftransplant through an intricate
OL,10,Fprocedure, saving his life after he
OL,11,Fcontracted a common childhood illness
OL,12,Fwhich made him seriously unwell as his
OL,13,Ftiny body was unable to fight off the
OL,14,Fbug.
OL,16,FHis mother Maisie Ransom has joined
OL,17,FNHS Blood and Transplant (NHSBT) to
OL,18,Fthank the donors who have donated for
OL,19,Fthis rare procedure ` also known as
OL,20,Fintrauterine transfusion (IUT).
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1776819790
OL,3,CFamily of UK's youngest blood
OL,4,Ctransfusion recipient express
OL,5,Cgratitude to donors
OL,7,FThe donation authority has identified
OL,8,Fthe eight donors whose blood has been
OL,9,Fused the most to make the product used
OL,10,Fin an IUT.
OL,12,FSeveral strict criteria must be met
OL,13,Ffor donors to be eligible to donate
OL,14,Ffor this rare procedure, which can be
OL,15,Fneeded when babies become extremely
OL,16,Funwell with anaemia before they are
OL,17,Fborn.
OL,19,FDonors need to be men, have type O
OL,20,Fblood which is "Kell negative" and
OL,21,Falso negative for cytomegalovirus.
OL,26,@|D@POU|D@^O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1776819790
OL,3,CFamily of UK's youngest blood
OL,4,Ctransfusion recipient express
OL,5,Cgratitude to donors
OL,7,FTheir blood is made into small packs
OL,8,Fof extremely concentrated red cells,
OL,9,Fwhich are then transfused via needle
OL,10,Fand guided by ultrasound.
OL,12,FOnly around 180 IUT units are issued
OL,13,Feach year by NHSBT.
OL,15,FThis procedure was used to help Arthur
OL,16,Fwhen he contracted parvovirus `
OL,17,Fslapped cheek syndrome ` while still
OL,18,Fin the womb.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1776819790
OL,3,CFamily of UK's youngest blood
OL,4,Ctransfusion recipient express
OL,5,Cgratitude to donors
OL,7,FThe virus is usually harmless to
OL,8,Fchildren but made Arthur extremely
OL,9,Funwell due to his immature immune
OL,10,Fsystem.
OL,12,FIt made him severely anaemic, leading
OL,13,Fto a dangerous build-up of fluid,
OL,14,Fwhich in turn led to Arthur having
OL,15,Fheart failure.
OL,17,FThe IUT was delivered at St George's
OL,18,FHospital in London in 2024, delivering
OL,19,Foxygen to Arthur's body so the fluid
OL,20,Faround his heart and organs could be
OL,21,Freabsorbed.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1776819790
OL,3,CFamily of UK's youngest blood
OL,4,Ctransfusion recipient express
OL,5,Cgratitude to donors
OL,7,FThis reduced the strain on his body
OL,8,Fand heart, allowing normal function to
OL,9,Freturn.
OL,11,FArthur was born in January 2025 and is
OL,12,Fnow "doing great".
OL,14,FHis mum said: "The experience was
OL,15,Fabsolutely terrifying.
OL,17,F"The doctor said it was 50/50 whether
OL,18,Fhe would make it or not. He was so
OL,19,Fsmall the doctors were working within
OL,20,Fmillimetres.
OL,26,@tD@EOUtD@QO]vD@OOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1776819790
OL,3,CFamily of UK's youngest blood
OL,4,Ctransfusion recipient express
OL,5,Cgratitude to donors
OL,7,F"Without that blood he would not have
OL,8,Fmade it ` his organs were failing, his
OL,9,Fheart was completely enveloped in
OL,10,Ffluid and it was struggling to pump.
OL,12,F"If nothing was done he would not have
OL,13,Fmade it much longer.
OL,15,F"The doctor said to the best of her
OL,16,Fknowledge there was no-one younger to
OL,17,Fget an intrauterine transfusion."
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@AOUwD@AOUyD@aO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1776819790
OL,3,CFamily of UK's youngest blood
OL,4,Ctransfusion recipient express
OL,5,Cgratitude to donors
OL,7,FThe 30-year-old primary school teacher
OL,8,Fadded: "Arthur's doing great now, he's
OL,9,Fa really chirpy little boy, reaching
OL,10,Fall the milestones.
OL,12,F"He keeps us on our toes.
OL,14,F"I think every day about how lucky I
OL,15,Fam.
OL,17,F"I don't think there are words to
OL,18,Fdescribe how thankful I am to blood
OL,19,Fdonors.
OL,26,@pD@HOUtD@AOUvD@AOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1776819790
OL,3,CFamily of UK's youngest blood
OL,4,Ctransfusion recipient express
OL,5,Cgratitude to donors
OL,7,F"To have the life I am now living,
OL,8,Fwith my family, there's no words to
OL,9,Fexpress the gratitude I feel and how
OL,10,Ffortunate I was to be able to access
OL,11,Fthat care and blood promptly.
OL,13,F"I do often wonder who the person to
OL,14,Fdonate was as I would love to tell
OL,15,Fthem that their decision to give blood
OL,16,Fgave my boy the chance to be here."
OL,18,FDr Anne Kelly, paediatric transfusion
OL,19,Fand components clinical expert for
OL,20,FNHSBT, said: "Intrauterine
OL,21,Ftransfusions are very rare.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOUxD@cO]|D@NOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1776819790
OL,3,CFamily of UK's youngest blood
OL,4,Ctransfusion recipient express
OL,5,Cgratitude to donors
OL,7,F"They are only done in specialised
OL,8,Funits when absolutely needed to help
OL,9,Fsave a life.
OL,11,F"We only supply from blood from
OL,12,Fcarefully selected donors and extra
OL,13,Fsafety measures are applied as the
OL,14,Fpatients are particularly vulnerable
OL,15,Frecipients because of their small size
OL,16,Fand developmental immaturity.
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G10/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1776819790
OL,3,CFamily of UK's youngest blood
OL,4,Ctransfusion recipient express
OL,5,Cgratitude to donors
OL,7,F"We're incredibly grateful to these
OL,8,Fdonors whose blood has been used the
OL,9,Fmost times for IUTs and we urge anyone
OL,10,Fwho has been inspired to consider
OL,11,Fregistering as a blood donor at
OL,12,Fblood.co.uk."
OL,14,FPaul Bickley, 45, who has been
OL,15,Fidentified as one of the men who has
OL,16,Fdonated the most for IUT procedures,
OL,17,Fsaid he started donating blood because
OL,18,Fof his mother's "generous heart".
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@MO]zD@QOUzD@`O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G11/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41712
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1776819790
OL,3,CFamily of UK's youngest blood
OL,4,Ctransfusion recipient express
OL,5,Cgratitude to donors
OL,7,FThe father of four, from Richmond, who
OL,8,Fis a vice president of an insurance
OL,9,Fcompany, said: "I started donating
OL,10,Fbecause my mum and dad donate.
OL,12,F"My mum told me it is a good thing to
OL,13,Fdo to give back literally and
OL,14,Fmetaphorically to society.
OL,16,F"She just has a generous heart.
OL,18,F"As the years went on and we had our
OL,19,Fown children I just realised life is
OL,20,Fvery precious and that kept me
OL,21,Fdonating.
OL,26,@qD@POUtD@AOUxD@AOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G12/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41713
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1776819790
OL,3,CFamily of UK's youngest blood
OL,4,Ctransfusion recipient express
OL,5,Cgratitude to donors
OL,7,F"Hearing my blood was used in this way
OL,8,Falmost made me cry, to think a very
OL,9,Fsmall act of kindness on my part could
OL,10,Fhave such a massive impact.
OL,12,F"It was mind-blowing and miraculous."
OL,14,FDavid Smith, 64, from Westminster in
OL,15,FLondon, has also been identified as a
OL,16,Fdonor whose blood has been used the
OL,17,Fmost for these specialist transfusions.
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@AOUtD@eO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G13/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41714
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1776819790
OL,3,CFamily of UK's youngest blood
OL,4,Ctransfusion recipient express
OL,5,Cgratitude to donors
OL,7,FThe retired heating and ventilation
OL,8,Fengineer, who has donated more than 80
OL,9,Ftimes overall, said: "When I found out
OL,10,FI was O negative I thought I would
OL,11,Fkeep doing this.
OL,13,F"You can't not do it if you can help
OL,14,Fbabies, you have to.
OL,16,F"It's always a pleasure to donate,
OL,17,Fwhether it's used for babies or for
OL,18,Fanyone."
OL,26,@qD@VOUuD@AOUxD@AOUzD@HO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G14/16
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
