OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41715
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1776819790
OL,3,CFamily of UK's youngest blood
OL,4,Ctransfusion recipient express
OL,5,Cgratitude to donors
OL,7,FDr Luci Etheridge, consultant
OL,8,Fpaediatrician and chief medical
OL,9,Fofficer at St George's, said: "For
OL,10,Fbabies like Arthur, a blood
OL,11,Ftransfusion while still in the womb
OL,12,Fcan mean the difference between life
OL,13,Fand loss.
OL,15,F"We are proud to provide this highly
OL,16,Fspecialised, lifesaving care at St
OL,17,FGeorge's, and are deeply grateful to
OL,18,Fthe donors whose generosity makes this
OL,19,Fpossible, as well as to NHS Blood and
OL,20,FTransplant for their vital and ongoing
OL,21,Fwork."
OL,26,@qD@_OUwD@AOU}D@FO]
